EffectTypes.description: Area of effect actions attack all targets within the AoE template.
Blockers apply crowd control effects which typically cause the target to be unable to perform some actions.
Healing effects restore damage or remove debilitating effects.
Miscellaneous buffs apply a beneficial effect to the bearer for a certain amount of time; reapplications of the effect reset the time but do not add to it.
Miscellaneous debuffs apply a detrimental effect to the bearer for a certain amount of time; reapplications of the effect reset the time but do not add to it.
Miscellaneous effects do variable things for the attack not covered by the other types.
Miscellaneous restrictions make the attack less effective or more dangerous to use in some way.

Stacking debuffs have an effect proportional to the number of stacks, and stacks are removed over time at a rate based on the bearers Recovery stat (i.e., lose stacks from all debuffs equal to Base Recovery plus that specific type of Recovery each round).
States are essentially Miscellaneous Debuffs that dont have an innate effect: they simply set up other attacks to have a greater effect.
